# pseudocron-medium.cfg.example — pgai-agent-kanban pseudocron schedule: MEDIUM tier
#
# Hardware assumption: 2-4 cores / 8-16 GB RAM, dedicated or semi-dedicated host.
#
# Tier: medium
# Cadence: every 2 minutes per agent, release-side on even minutes,
#   work-producers on odd minutes.
#   - PM     fires at even minutes: 0,2,4,...,58
#   - CM     fires at even minutes: 0,2,4,...,58
#   - TESTER fires at even minutes: 0,2,4,...,58
#   - CODER  fires at odd  minutes: 1,3,5,...,59
#   - WRITER fires at odd  minutes: 1,3,5,...,59
#
# Crontab-to-pseudocron mapping:
#   crontab-medium uses sub-minute sleep staggers to spread agents within
#   each 2-minute window.  Pseudocron has no sleep/stagger field; sub-minute
#   offsets are collapsed to minute granularity:
#
#     crontab: PM     */2  --sleep=0   -> even minutes (0,2,...,58)  [unchanged]
#     crontab: CM     */2  --sleep=21  -> even+21s; collapsed to even minutes
#     crontab: TESTER */2  --sleep=42  -> even+42s; collapsed to even minutes
#     crontab: CODER  1-59/2 --sleep=0  -> odd minutes (1,3,...,59) [unchanged]
#     crontab: WRITER 1-59/2 --sleep=21 -> odd+21s; collapsed to odd minutes
#
#   Result: PM, CM, and TESTER all fire at the same even minutes; CODER and
#   WRITER fire at the same odd minutes.  wake-batch.sh's own work-queue
#   locking handles serialization when multiple agents fire simultaneously.
#
# Maximum agent-to-agent handoff latency: ~2 minutes (next even/odd cycle).
# Best-case handoff (work-producer -> release-side): 1 minute.
# Recommended for: developer workstations, small team VMs, 2-4 core servers.
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# REQUIRED pseudocron.env EXPORTS
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# When paired with install-pseudocron.sh, pseudocron.env must contain:
#
#   export PGAI_AGENT_KANBAN_ROOT_PATH=/path/to/pgai_agent_kanban
#       # Full path to the installed kanban root.  All wake scripts derive
#       # their paths from this variable.
#
#   export PATH=/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin
#       # Ensure wake-batch.sh and its dependencies are on PATH.
#       # Adjust if claude or other tools are installed to non-standard paths.
#
#   export HOME=/home/your-user
#       # Required when pseudocron is launched from a system init (systemd unit,
#       # etc.) that does not set HOME.  Wake scripts and claude may need HOME.
#
#   export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=<your-api-key>
#       # Anthropic API key consumed by claude.  Required unless the API key
#       # is injected via another mechanism (e.g. a secrets manager wrapper).
#
# Optional: override a role's model (per-role; provider-agnostic)
#   export PGAI_CODER_MODEL=<model-id>
#   export PGAI_PM_MODEL=<model-id>
#       # Recognized roles: PM, CODER, WRITER, TESTER, CM
#
# Copy team/scripts/pseudocron.env.example to
# $PGAI_AGENT_KANBAN_ROOT_PATH/pseudocron.env and fill in real values.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Install:
#   cp team/templates/install/pseudocron-medium.cfg.example \
#      "$PGAI_AGENT_KANBAN_ROOT_PATH/pseudocron.cfg"
#   # Then edit to set the correct KANBAN_ROOT value in each command.
#
# Replacement token:  Replace __KANBAN_ROOT__ with the real kanban root path
# before installing, e.g.:
#   sed "s|__KANBAN_ROOT__|/home/rocky/pgai_agent_kanban|g" \
#     team/templates/install/pseudocron-medium.cfg.example \
#     > "$PGAI_AGENT_KANBAN_ROOT_PATH/pseudocron.cfg"

# =============================================================================
# MEDIUM-TIER PATTERN — every-2-minutes, release-side on even, work-producers
#                       on odd (sub-minute staggers collapsed to minute offsets)
# =============================================================================
# Maximum wait between agent firings: ~2 minutes
# Best-case agent-to-agent handoff: 1 minute (odd->even or even->odd boundary)
#
# Operator tuning:
#   - Swap CODER/WRITER to even minutes and PM/CM/TESTER to odd if preferred.
#   - Add 1-minute spread within a group by shifting a subset by 1 minute
#     (e.g., PM at even, CM at odd, TESTER at even+2) if lock contention occurs.

# --- Even-minute agents (release-side: PM, CM, TESTER) ---
# All three fire at the same even minutes. wake-batch.sh serializes via
# work-queue locking.

# PM fires every 2 minutes at even minutes: 0,2,4,...,58
