# =============================================================================
# MAINTENANCE JOBS
# =============================================================================
# Note: pseudocron fires a job every time the matching minute occurs within
# each hour.  Unlike cron, it has no day-of-week or hour field.  The cleanup
# jobs below fire once per hour at the listed minute.  For weekly/daily
# semantics, use a wrapper script that checks the current date/time before
# running, or schedule these jobs via cron alongside pseudocron.

# --- Cleanup script (fires hourly at minute 0; use a date-guard wrapper
#     for weekly semantics equivalent to crontab's "0 4 * * 0") ---
# 0 __KANBAN_ROOT__/scripts/cleanup/cleanup.sh >> __KANBAN_ROOT__/logs/cron-cleanup.log 2>&1

# --- Log cleanup (fires hourly at minute 30; use a date-guard wrapper
#     for daily semantics equivalent to crontab's "30 4 * * *") ---
# 30 __KANBAN_ROOT__/scripts/cleanup/cleanup_logs.sh >> __KANBAN_ROOT__/logs/cron-cleanup-logs.log 2>&1
